4.00	Pavel_Schilling	Pavel Schilling	Baron Pavel L'vovitch Schilling, also known as Paul Schilling (b. ca. 1780, Reval –now, Tallinn, Estonia – d. St. Petersburg, Russia, 25 July 1837), was a diplomat of Baltic German origin employed in the service of Russia in Germany, and who built a pioneering electrical telegraph. It consisted of a single needle system which used a telegraph code to indicate the characters in a message.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/c/ca/Pavel_Shilling.jpg
